<paragraph id="E8403669FF8CFFF0FE5F1FC98609B7D4" blockId="27.[454,861,1476,1503]" box="[454,861,1476,1503]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">
<heading id="B3088105FF8CFFF0FE5F1FC98609B7D4" box="[454,861,1476,1503]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF8CFFF0FE5F1FC98609B7D4" authority="(Uhler, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Uhler" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[454,861,1476,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Mesovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoena">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF8CFFF0FE5F1FC987E3B7D4" bold="true" box="[454,695,1476,1503]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Mesovelia amoena</emphasis>
(Uhler, 1894)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF8CFFF0FF591FF785ACB4CB" blockId="27.[160,1156,1530,1728]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">
This mesoveliid water strider is reported from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FD5B1FF787ABB418" box="[706,767,1530,1555]" name="Cuba" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FC911FF78630B418" box="[776,868,1530,1555]" name="Jamaica" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FCF51FF786BBB418" box="[876,1007,1530,1555]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, and some of the Lesser Antilles, as well as being widespread through the Americas (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8CFFF0FC5D1C108409B453" author="de Kort-Gommer M &amp; Nieser N" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" pagination="72 - 87" refId="ref24300" refString="de Kort-Gommer M, Nieser N. 1969. Records of Antillean water striders (Heteroptera). Stud Fauna Curacao Carib Isl. 30: 72 - 87." type="journal article" year="1969">de Kort-Gommer and Nieser 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8CFFF0FEF41C32871FB453" author="Naranjo C &amp; Munoz Riviaux S &amp; Figueiredo Moreira FF &amp; Correa Court R" box="[365,587,1599,1624]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" pagination="897 - 907" refId="ref27678" refString="Naranjo C, Munoz Riviaux S, Figueiredo Moreira FF, Correa Court R. 2010. Taxonomy and distribution of aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Insecta) from Cuba. Rev Biol Trop. 58 (3): 897 - 907. doi: 10.15517 / rbt. v 58 i 2.5253." type="journal article" year="2010">Naranjo et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF8CFFF0FDC51C3286D7B453" author="Lanigan AC &amp; Hyslop EJ" box="[604,899,1599,1624]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826" pagination="295 - 297" refId="ref26282" refString="Lanigan AC, Hyslop EJ. 2011. The aquatic and semiaquatic Hemiptera of Jamaica. J Freshw Ecol. 26 (2): 295 - 297. doi: 10.1080 / 02705060.2011.559335." type="journal article" year="2011">Lanigan and Hyslop 2011</bibRefCitation>
). We present the first records of this species from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF8CFFF0FD981C6F87C3B470" box="[513,663,1634,1659]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
; it was found on St. Thomas in ghuts, ponds, and mangrove brackish pools and streams, although not as abundant as the following species.
</paragraph>
